SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
Article – Health Occupations
1A–302.
(a) To qualify for a license, an applicant shall be an individual who meets the
requirements of this section.
(b) The applicant shall:
(4) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2027, SUBMIT TO A CRIMINAL HISTORY
RECORDS CHECK IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 1A–302.1 OF THIS SUBTITLE;
[(4)] (5) Demonstrate the ability to communicate in the English
language; and
[(5)] (6) Meet any other qualifications that the Board establishes in
